l":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/40/Colorado_State_Highway_65.JPG","cap":"Colorado State Highway 65","desc":"Colorado State Highway 65, which forms part of the Grand Mesa Scenic and Historic Byway, in Mesa County, Colorado.","credit":"Jeffrey Beall · CC BY-SA 3.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Colorado_State_Highway_65.JPG"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Colorado_Routes_92_and_65.jpg/1280px-Colorado_Routes_92_and_65.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/80/Colorado_Routes_92_and_65.jpg","cap":"Colorado Routes 92 and 65","desc":"Colorado State Highway 92 at junction with Colorado State Highway 65.","credit":"Doug Kerr · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Colorado_Routes_92_and_65.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Cory%2C_Colorado.JPG/1280px-Cory%2C_Colorado.JPG","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8c/Cory%2C_Colorado.JPG","cap":"Cory, Colorado","desc":"A view of Cory, Colorado , a neighborhood of Orchard City . The picture shows the Cory General Store and U.S. Post Office at 9340 Highway 65, Cory, Colorado 81414.","credit":"Jeffrey Beall · CC BY 4.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Cory,_Colorado.JPG"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Mesa%2C_Colorado.JPG/1280px-Mesa%2C_Colorado.JPG","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2b/Mesa%2C_Colorado.JPG","cap":"Mesa, Colorado","desc":"A view of Mesa, Colorado in Mesa County, Colorado . The north face of the Grand Mesa lies in the distance. The road is Colorado State Highway 65 , which serves as Mesa's main street.","credit":"Jeffrey Beall · CC BY 4.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mesa,_Colorado.JPG"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Grand_Mesa_Summit.JPG/1280px-Grand_Mesa_Summit.JPG","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/66/Grand_Mesa_Summit.JPG","cap":"Grand Mesa Summit","desc":"The Grand Mesa Summit, elevation 10,839 feet (3,304 m), on the border between Mesa and Delta counties in western Colorado. The road is Colorado State Highway 65 , and the view is towards the south.","credit":"Jeffrey Beall · CC BY 4.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Grand_Mesa_Summit.JPG"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/eb/Colorado_-_Berthoud_Pass.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/eb/Colorado_-_Berthoud_Pass.jpg","cap":"Colorado Berthoud Pass","desc":"U.S. highway 40 near Berthoud Pass, in the Rocky Mountains, The summit is 11,307 ft (3,446 m). It is on the Continental Divide, so water to the west flows to the Pacific Ocean, and to the east flows to the Atlantic basin. Berthoud Pass is about 40 miles (65 km) west of Denver.","credit":"Roger Wollstadt from Sarasota, Florida · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Colorado_-_Berthoud_Pass.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6d/View_of_Colorado_State_Highway_82_east_from_Independence_Pass.jpg/1280px-View_of_Colorado_State_Highway_82_east_from_Independence_Pass.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6d/View_of_Colorado_State_Highway_82_east_from_Independence_Pass.jpg","cap":"View of Colorado State Highway 82 east from Independence Pass","desc":"View east from scenic overlook along Colorado State Highway 82","credit":"Rick Kimpel from Spring, TX, USA, Cropped and color-correcte · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:View_of_Colorado_State_Highway_82_east_from_Independence_Pass.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Mt_Sopris_from_Colorado_State_Highway_82.jpg/1280px-Mt_Sopris_from_Colorado_State_Highway_82.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2c/Mt_Sopris_from_Colorado_State_Highway_82.jpg","cap":"M